{"schema_version":"1.7.3","id":"OESA-2024-1759","published":"2024-06-28T11:08:20Z","modified":"2025-09-03T06:18:19.012039Z","upstream":["CVE-2022-3341"],"summary":"ffmpeg security update","details":"FFmpeg is a complete and free Internet live audio and video broadcasting solution for Linux/Unix. It also includes a digital VCR. It can encode in real time in many formats including MPEG1 audio and video, MPEG4, h263, ac3, asf, avi, real, mjpeg, and flash.\r\n\r\nSecurity Fix(es):\r\n\r\nA null pointer dereference issue was discovered in &apos;FFmpeg&apos; in decode_main_header() function of libavformat/nutdec.c file. The flaw occurs because the function lacks check of the return value of avformat_new_stream() and triggers the null pointer dereference error, causing an application to crash.(CVE-2022-3341)","affected":[{"package":{"name":"ffmpeg","ecosystem":"openEuler:20.03-LTS-SP4","purl":"pkg:rpm/openEuler/ffmpeg&distro=openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP4"},"ranges":[{"type":"ECOSYSTEM","events":[{"introduced":"0"},{"fixed":"4.2.4-7.oe2003sp4"}]}],"ecosystem_specific":{"aarch64":["libavdevice-4.2.4-7.oe2003sp4.aarch64.rpm","ffmpeg-devel-4.2.4-7.oe2003sp4.aarch64.rpm","ffmpeg-4.2.4-7.oe2003sp4.aarch64.rpm","ffmpeg-libs-4.2.4-7.oe2003sp4.aarch64.rpm","ffmpeg-debuginfo-4.2.4-7.oe2003sp4.aarch64.rpm","ffmpeg-debugsource-4.2.4-7.oe2003sp4.aarch64.rpm"],"src":["ffmpeg-4.2.4-7.oe2003sp4.src.rpm"],"x86_64":["ffmpeg-debuginfo-4.2.4-7.oe2003sp4.x86_64.rpm","ffmpeg-debugsource-4.2.4-7.oe2003sp4.x86_64.rpm","ffmpeg-libs-4.2.4-7.oe2003sp4.x86_64.rpm","libavdevice-4.2.4-7.oe2003sp4.x86_64.rpm","ffmpeg-devel-4.2.4-7.oe2003sp4.x86_64.rpm","ffmpeg-4.2.4-7.oe2003sp4.x86_64.rpm"]},"database_specific":{"source":"https://repo.openeuler.org/security/data/osv/OESA-2024-1759.json"}}],"references":[{"type":"ADVISORY","url":"https://www.openeuler.org/en/security/safety-bulletin/detail.html?id=openEuler-SA-2024-1759"},{"type":"ADVISORY","url":"https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2022-3341"}],"database_spe